news.title: Hong Kong audit regulator expands probe into Evergrande's unit
news.para: The Financial Reporting Council (FRC) said in a statement it was investigating the 2020 and first half of 2021 financial statements of Evergrande Property Services, as well as the audit carried out by PwC on its 2020 annual accounts.

news.title: Supertech to repair 10 more pillars near twin towers; charging of Ceyane to be done first
news.para: The developer will not conduct any separate structural audit of the buildings of its own but rely on the report of the private consultant that was hired by the Emerald Court RWA earlier this year to assess the damage to the columns.

news.title: Chinese developers in 'survival mode' slash property investment
news.para: Property investment in July fell 12.3% year-on-year, the biggest decline in 2022, while new construction starts by floor area slumped 45.4%, the largest drop since January-February 2013, according to Reuters calculations based on data from the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) on Monday.

news.title: Emaar Properties to discuss selling its e-commerce business
news.para: The meeting, disclosed in a statement, will be held a week after Emaar announced a $2 billion cash and stock buyout of a joint venture partner in one of its real estate projects.

news.title: Over 700 flats in Delhi's Kathputli Colony to be handed over soon
news.para: Nearly 2,800 families will be given flats which are being developed as a public-private-partnership (PPP) between the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) and Raheja Developers.

news.title: Maharashtra SCDRC orders Siddharth Construction to refund buyer's money with 21% interest
news.para: The couple told the commission that they had come across an advertisement in the local newspaper regarding construction of a building at Salphadevi Pada, Mulund West.

news.title: Hines forays into Mumbai; to develop nine lakh sq ft office building in tie up with local player
news.para: This building, part of an 8.8-acre mixed-use development, is scheduled to break ground in the first quarter of 2023 and be completed in the fourth quarter of 2025.

news.title: SBI raises benchmark lending rates by up to 50 basis points
news.para: External Benchmark based Lending Rate (EBLR) and Repo-Linked Lending Rate (RLLR) have been raised by 50 basis points while the hike in Marginal Cost of funds-based Lending Rate (MCLR) is 20 basis points across all tenure.

news.title: Mumbai: East Indians seek extra FSI to house growing families in gaothans
news.para: Clusters of charming cottages and Portuguese-style homes, some dating back to the 19th century, are the last remaining vestiges of Mumbai’s urban gaothans or villages, now surrounded by high-rise structures.

news.title: Nagpur civic body clears a building plan in record four days
news.para: The measure has been taken following the bogus contracts scam which was effected after ‘misusing’ username and password of a few staff members.

news.title: Six town planning schemes in Pune region to see light of day this fiscal
news.para: Of the total six, the work on the Mann Mhalunge town planning scheme has already commenced, said officials.

news.title: Day 2 of charging: Six Supertech twin tower floors fitted with explosives
news.para: Officials in Edifice Engineering, the company tasked with bringing down the two towers, said three additional floors in Ceyane had been partially fitted with explosives.

news.title: Prestige Estates aims to sell properties worth Rs 12,000 crore this fiscal
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects Ltd has a strong presence in South India and the company has made its foray into Mumbai market.

news.title: Amrapali homebuyers oppose court receiver's plan to sell unused FAR
news.para: Hundreds of buyers from different Amrapali projects gathered at a park in Techzone 4 and raised slogans against the proposal.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: First batch of explosives reaches site amid tight security
news.para: More than 3,500 kg of explosives will be filled in around 9,400 holes drilled in the columns and shears of the skeletal structures of the twin towers which will be razed to the ground.
